snippet.textDisplay: Pewds! I may be able to explain the VAT logic a little more... And it'll make you more pissed... So the reason the gov't does that is because, even though they KNOW you don't historically owe that money on your business, when you give them that money to hold onto until their eventual refund of it, the gov't invests that money in different ways and accrues interest on that money that you gave them... Interest that you would have made on that money had you kept it yourself. So it's a way for them to still make money off of the fact that you own a business without ACTUALLY taxing you (since they refund it). But as you know, you still end up, in a sense, losing money because of the slight inflation between the time you gave them the money and the time you get that money back. Now... I know it's not a huge deal, but it is frustrating knowing that they're doing this and being sneaky instead of just saying "hey, pay us this amount of money so that we can build infrastructure and increase education, etc"
